Super campus and the food provided over there is too cheap and the best quality. The International Institute of Information Technology, Bangalore commonly known as IIIT Bangalore and also IIITB is a graduate school situated in Bangalore, Karnataka, India.

The campus is beautiful, with lots of greenery around. The faculty here is top notch with PhD from top universities of the world. The institute offers 6 research areas like data science, networking, computer science etc.  The curriculum is flexible and can be planned as per the interest of the student. Though there are few mandatory courses for initial years. College also has tie-ups with leading organisations that have set up their labs in the college. Also, college has helped in setting up Myanmar institute of information technology with the help of Ministry of foreign affairs. Also, in a recent MOU signed by Indian Prime Minister with Indonesia, a group from Indonesia will be soon enrolling in the college of fully sponsored studies. College professors has vast experience in their area of interest, with lots of research paper in top conferences across the world. One student from the college is also going to join Harvard University for pursuing his PhD. Also, college has a good coding culture with two time ACM icpc finalists. One of the students from imtech batch is joining Google brain in the US. The college provides overall growth, with good number of sports facilities, even though the campus is small. The hostels are also very well maintained, with 24 hour power back. The college administration is also very cooperative to student affairs, we have student activity council for handling student affairs. The college can be reached directly from the airport by shuttle service.
